<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id46d50601-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s6341"><num value="6341">§ 6341.</num><heading> Expense of levy and sale</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall determine the expenses to be allowed in all cases of levy and sale.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id46d50602-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/789">68A Stat. 789</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/455/tXIX/s1906/b/13/A">Pub. L. 94–455, title XIX, § 1906(b)(13)(A)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-04">Oct. 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/1834">90 Stat. 1834</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
